The intra- and inter-assay CVs obtained for PON1 measurement with PA and TBBL and for TAC analysis are shown in Table 1
. Intra-assay CVs were lower than 10% in all cases. Inter-assay CVs were lower than 7%, 16% and 12% for PA, TBBL and TAC, respectively. Coefficient of linear regression higher than 0.98 was observed when pooled serum was diluted and analyzed with any of the validated methods (Fig. 1
). The calculated limits of detection were 0.64 U/ml, 0.04 U/ml and 0.02 mmol/l for PA, TBBL and TAC, respectively.
